nt":12,"restaurantCount":14,"bestTimeToVisit":"Visit from June to August for island hopping and maritime activities.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1748814670185-ae3f3b8fee7d?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxLYXN0ZWxob2xtJTIwY2FzdGxlJTIwbWVkaWV2YWx8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzc2NTc4NHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Tannis Sullivan"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1748814670185-ae3f3b8fee7d?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxLYXN0ZWxob2xtJTIwY2FzdGxlJTIwbWVkaWV2YWx8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzc2NTc4NHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"}],"top10":[{"rank":1,"name":"Helsinki","placeId":"helsinki","regionId":"uusimaa","regionName":"Uusimaa","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544096714-18ad573ad07e?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxIZWxzaW5raSUyMENhdGhlZHJhbCUyMEZpbmxhbmR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzcxNjE4NHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Tapio Haaja"},"description":"Finland's vibrant capital city sits on the Baltic coast and is known for its distinctive neoclassical and modern architecture, including the iconic white Uspenski Cathedral and the striking Temppeliaukio Church built into a rock. The city offers world-class museums, design districts, excellent dining, and waterfront promenades that make it the cultural heart of Finland."},{"rank":2,"name":"Turku","placeId":"turku","regionId":"uusimaa","regionName":"Uusimaa","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1671366660419-ac19856a6ebf?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUdXJrdSUyMENhc3RsZSUyMEZpbmxhbmR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzcxNjE5M3ww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Juho Luomala"},"description":"Located at the mouth of the Turku River, this historic city is Finland's former capital and serves as a cultural gateway to the Archipelago region with its impressive castle, riverside setting, and vibrant student atmosphere. Though technically in Southwest Finland, it's often visited from Uusimaa as a major regional hub."},{"rank":3,"name":"Tampere","placeId":"tampere","regionId":"pirkanmaa","regionName":"Pirkanmaa","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1670575883083-ea9022ec3599?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUYW1wZXJlJTIwY2l0eSUyMEZpbmxhbmR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzcxNjQwM3ww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Veikko Venemies"},"description":"Finland's second-largest city, known for its vibrant culture, museums, and industrial heritage between two lakes. Essential for art galleries, design shops, restaurants, and the iconic Särkänniemi amusement park complex."},{"rank":4,"name":"Rovaniemi","placeId":"rovaniemi","regionId":"lapland","regionName":"Lapland","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1637138768589-932e383c0f39?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxSb3ZhbmllbWklMjBBcmN0aWMlMjBDaXJjbGV8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzc2NTcyMnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Tom Brunberg"},"description":"The capital of Lapland and gateway to the Arctic, famous as the official home of Santa Claus with the Santa Claus Village attracting hundreds of thousands annually. It's the largest city in the region with excellent infrastructure, museums, and as the crossing point of the Arctic Circle, it embodies the mystique of the far north."},{"rank":5,"name":"Oulu","placeId":"oulu","regionId":"north_ostrobothnia","regionName":"North Ostrobothnia","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1657123096362-f12bfb5dcf53?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxPdWx1JTIwY2l0eSUyMHNreWxpbmUlMjBGaW5sYW5kfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM3NjA2Mjd8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Janne Leimola"},"description":"Finland's largest city north of the Arctic Circle and the capital of North Ostrobothnia, Oulu is a vibrant hub of technology, culture, and northern innovation. The city offers excellent museums, a lively downtown scene, and serves as the gateway to Arctic experiences."},{"rank":6,"name":"Savonlinna","placeId":"savonlinna","regionId":"south_karelia","regionName":"South Karelia","image":null,"description":"Though technically in North Karelia, this nearby lake city is famous for Olavinlinna Castle and the annual opera festival held within its medieval walls. The castle sits dramatically on an island and is one of Finland's most iconic historical landmarks."},{"rank":7,"name":"Nuuksio National Park","placeId":"nuuksio","regionId":"uusimaa","regionName":"Uusimaa","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1632430318640-c827bb97acf4?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxOdXVrc2lvJTIwTmF0aW9uYWwlMjBQYXJrJTIwRmlubGFuZHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNzE2MjAxfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Gabriella Clare Marino"},"description":"Located just outside Espoo, this magnificent national park offers diverse hiking trails through boreal forest with scenic lakes, rocky outcrops, and pristine wilderness only minutes from Helsinki. The park is perfect for experiencing authentic Finnish nature with opportunities for swimming, picnicking, and peaceful forest walks."},{"rank":8,"name":"Jyväskylä","placeId":"jyvaskyla","regionId":"central_finland","regionName":"Central Finland","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593947594099-fa3e046c32ea?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxKeXYlQzMlQTRza3lsJUMzJUE0JTIwY2l0eSUyMEZpbmxhbmR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzc1ODUwOHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"K8"},"description":"Central Finland's largest city and cultural heart, known for its distinctive Alvar Aalto architecture and vibrant arts scene. Home to museums, galleries, universities, and excellent dining that make it the region's essential urban hub."},{"rank":9,"name":"Finnish Lake Region","placeId":"lakeland","regionId":"paijat_hame","regionName":"Päijät-Häme","image":null,"description":"Spanning central and eastern Finland, the interconnected lake system is the world's largest concentration of lakes, creating a unique landscape ideal for cottage rentals, boating, and water activities. Visitors come to experience the quintessential Finnish summer lifestyle, pristine waterways, and peaceful nature-based tourism."},{"rank":10,"name":"Kuopio","placeId":"kuopio","regionId":"north_savo","regionName":"North Savo","image":null,"description":"The largest city in North Savo, Kuopio is a vibrant university hub on the shores of Lake Kallavesi known for its distinctive Puijo Tower offering panoramic views. The city combines modern culture with traditional Finnish charm, featuring excellent museums, restaurants serving local Karelian cuisine, and a lively marketplace."}]}